    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sr-(Methionyl sh-Oligopeptide-99) is a single chain recombinant peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from sh-Oligopeptide-99 with the initiation code for methionine. The fusion peptide contains 42 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
